<P>
   BOX-HOLYFIELD-REFEREE _ SPRINGFIELD, Ohio _ Vaughn Bean's
promoter has said he plans to file a protest against referee Brian
Garry over his officiating of Bean's championship bout against
Evander Holyfield last Saturday. But Garry has beaten him to the
punch and already filed his own official protest against the
promoter, Butch Lewis, for his conduct during the fight, the
president of the International Boxing Federation said. (Freeman,
Springfield News-Sun) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBC-SAT _ An NCAA four-year study of college entrance exam
scores for college football players confirms what we may have
suspected _ teams with lower test scores do better on the field
than those with higher scores. Coach Gerry Dirnardo, who has been
on both sides of the fence at Vandy and now at LSU, says classroom
intelligence does not always transfer to football smarts, while
other coaches say that because of the culturally biased tests,
bright kids don't always do well. Then there is Stanford, which has
excelled in both areas. (Fish, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 55.
WITH ILLUSTRATION
</P>
