<SLUG> BC-FBC-GATECH-PLAYER-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    How a player juggle football and academics
 &HT;    By Carroll Rogers
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Justin Robertson
</P>
<P>
   Georgia Tech
</P>
<P>
   -- Position: Backup inside linebacker.
</P>
<P>
   -- Class: Fourth-year senior.
</P>
<P>
   -- Major: Mechanical engineering.
</P>
<P>
   -- Class load: Four courses for 12 hours (15 to 17 outside of
football season).
</P>
<P>
   -- Class days: Monday, Wednesday, Friday.
</P>
<P>
   -- Courses: History of science and technology; statistics and
applications; fluid mechanics; dynamics II.
</P>
<P>
   -- Offseason class load: 15 to 17 hours; tries to schedule
tougher courses in winter and spring.
</P>
<P>
   A typical Wednesday of Justin Robertson
</P>
<P>
   7 a.m.: Awakens, eats breakfast.
</P>
<P>
   8 a.m.: First class.
</P>
<P>
   9 a.m.: Second class.
</P>
<P>
   10 a.m.: Goes to library to study or read newspaper.
</P>
<P>
   11 a.m.: Third class.
</P>
<P>
   Noon: Eats lunch, watches football film.
</P>
<P>
   1 p.m.: Fourth class.
</P>
<P>
   2 p.m.: Gets taped for practice.
</P>
<P>
   2:30 p.m.: Football meetings.
</P>
<P>
   3:50 p.m.: Practice.
</P>
<P>
   6:15 p.m.: Showers, eats dinner.
</P>
<P>
   7:30 p.m.: Tutoring at academic center.
</P>
<P>
   9:30 p.m.: Returns to room, studies.
</P>
<P>
   Midnight or later: Goes to sleep.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT
</P>
<P>
   ``During the week, pretty much school and football are all you
have time to worry about. It's harder than I thought it would be.
Coming out of high school, I had pretty good grades. I came here,
and it's sometimes a struggle. .. You have to take care of your
business and make sure you stay eligible. I'm getting my school for
free; that's my advantage.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
