 &LR; Oct. 31 in Atlantic City. ``The Prince doesn't dodge,'' he said.
Instead, he claimed he'd never agreed to fight McKinney, although
negotiations are ongoing. The best fight on that HBO card may be
International Boxing Federation super bantamweight champion  &UR; Vuyani
Bungu  &LR; (35-2, 18 KOs) vs.  &UR; Danny Romero  &LR; (32-3, 28 KOs) ...
Although De La Hoya's intention in their rematch was to destroy the
legend of Chavez, the WBC welterweight champion acknowledged that
it made him uneasy to watch middleweight champion  &UR; William Joppy
 &LR; do the same to 47-year-old  &UR; Roberto Duran  &LR; several weeks ago. ``It
was a sad event,'' De La Hoya said. ``It's very sad to see a
fighter of that status have to be beat down like that. But I'm
looking to beat down Chavez with no remorse whatsoever. That's my
job.'' Arum added similar feelings of unease about the beating
Duran took, saying, ``It tears your heart out. I made Duran $10
million after taxes in nine months and he's still broke. To see him
in that charade was terrible. He hasn't been able to fight since he
fought  &UR; Iran Barkley &LR; . It was awful. It's like  &UR; George Foreman  &LR; and
 &UR; Larry Holmes  &LR; (who fight Jan. 23 at the Astrodome). They can't
fight anybody real anymore.''
</P>
