be allowed to move into the mandatory position at junior
welterweight. That would guarantee him first shot at the winner of
the  &UR; Miguel Angel Gonzalez &LR; - &UR; Kostya Tszyu  &LR; Nov. 28 fight for the
vacant title ... Sometimes a guy should be left well enough alone.
Last week in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, British amateur champion
 &UR; Audley Harrison  &LR; was ordered to remove his personal boxing gloves
and wear new ones minutes before entering the ring in the super
heavyweight title fight of the Commonwealth Games. Angered,
Harrison walked out and KO'd  &UR; Michael Macaque  &LR; in 65 seconds.
Harrison claimed the gloves were so tight they crimped his hand and
prevented him from making a fist. ``That really got me more angry
but it worked to my advantage because I went looking for it with
bad intentions,'' he said.
</P>
