<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On deck: New York Mets
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 1:10 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV/Radio: Fox Sports South, WSB 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP Armando Reynoso (7-2, 3.24; 0-6,
6.37 lifetime vs. Braves) vs. RHP Greg Maddux (17-9, 2.24; 21-12,
3.47 lifetime vs. Mets).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Greg Maddux still leads the National League in ERA, has
thrown the most shutouts in the league (five), allowed the third
lowest batting average in the league (.220), leads the Braves staff
in strikeouts (201), in innings pitched (245) as well as complete
games (nine). So what's wrong with this picture? He has lost three
straight, is 5-7 in the second half and has accumulated a 5.40 ERA
in his last six starts. The worst hitting club in the majors, the
Arizona Diamondbacks, knocked him for 10 hits and five runs in his
last outing. The record is not all his fault. The Braves failed to
score more than three runs in any of his seven second-half losses.
Five times, they scored two or fewer and twice, they were shut out.
But he enters the day having allowed four earned runs in his last
16 1/3 innings. Reynoso has never beaten Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
